ordinary velocity, but rather the mass by the relativistic velocity.

2490
01:45:17,806 --> 01:45:24,306
So, the right definition in relativity theory is that p mu

2491
01:45:24,306 --> 01:45:30,806
with four components is equal to the mass times u mu.

2492
01:45:30,806 --> 01:45:35,056
That's four components. Momentum in

2493
01:45:35,056 --> 01:45:39,306
non-relativistic physics only had three components,

2494
01:45:39,306 --> 01:45:42,306
but it's interesting to ask what the fourth component is.

2495
01:45:42,306 --> 01:45:45,306
I'll tell you next time how you use the momentum.

2496
01:45:45,306 --> 01:45:47,306
You use the momentum

2497
01:45:47,306 --> 01:45:49,306
because it's conserved.

2498
01:45:49,306 --> 01:45:52,056
If you want to know what happens to particles when

2499
01:45:52,056 --> 01:45:54,806
they collide or particles when they decay and so forth,

2500
01:45:54,806 --> 01:45:57,806
the basic tool is conservation of momentum.

2501
01:45:57,806 --> 01:46:00,806
But not conservation of three components of

2502
01:46:00,806 --> 01:46:03,806
momentum, but conservation of all four components.

2503
01:46:03,806 --> 01:46:06,806
So, we ought to find out

2504
01:46:06,806 --> 01:46:09,806
what the fourth component of momentum is.

2505
01:46:09,806 --> 01:46:11,806
What about the first three components?

2506
01:46:11,806 --> 01:46:13,806
p x, let's say.

2507
01:46:13,806 --> 01:46:15,806
That's m times u x,

2508
01:46:15,806 --> 01:46:16,806
which is

2509
01:46:16,806 --> 01:46:17,306
m

2510
01:46:17,306 --> 01:46:19,306
times v x

2511
01:46:19,306 --> 01:46:21,306
divided by square root of 1

2512
01:46:21,306 --> 01:46:23,306
minus v squared over c squared.

2513
01:46:23,306 --> 01:46:24,306
Okay.

2514
01:46:24,306 --> 01:46:27,306
If v is small,

2515
01:46:27,306 --> 01:46:29,306
1 minus v squared over

2516
01:46:29,306 --> 01:46:31,306
c squared is basically just 1,

2517
01:46:31,306 --> 01:46:34,306
and so, for small velocity,

2518
01:46:34,306 --> 01:46:36,306
the momentum is just mv.

2519
01:46:36,306 --> 01:46:37,306
Alright?

2520
01:46:37,306 --> 01:46:39,306
As the velocity gets bigger and bigger,

2521
01:46:39,306 --> 01:46:42,806
the momentum starts changing and

2522
01:46:42,806 --> 01:46:46,306
deviating away from just mv.

2523
01:46:46,306 --> 01:46:46,806
In fact, it gets bigger than just mv.

2524
01:46:46,806 --> 01:46:51,806
But for small velocities, it's just a good old momentum.

2525
01:46:51,806 --> 01:46:53,806
What about the time component?

2526
01:46:53,806 --> 01:46:55,806
This is something new.

2527
01:46:55,806 --> 01:46:56,806
Or is it?

2528
01:46:56,806 --> 01:47:01,806
What about the time component, or equivalently p zero?

2529
01:47:01,806 --> 01:47:03,806
What is it?

2530
01:47:03,806 --> 01:47:04,806
Alright.

2531
01:47:04,806 --> 01:47:06,806
It's energy.

2532
01:47:06,806 --> 01:47:08,806
Energy is also conserved.

2533
01:47:08,806 --> 01:47:12,806
And the fourth component of the momentum vector is energy.

2534
01:47:12,806 --> 01:47:14,806
Let's see if we can see why that's true.

2535
01:47:14,806 --> 01:47:17,806
First of all,

2536
01:47:17,806 --> 01:47:20,806
it's m

2537
01:47:20,806 --> 01:47:23,806
divided by the square root of 1 minus v squared.

2538
01:47:23,806 --> 01:47:27,806
And let's put in the speeds of light now.

2539
01:47:27,806 --> 01:47:28,806
Now, I lied to you a little bit.

2540
01:47:28,806 --> 01:47:32,806
I said that pt is energy.

2541
01:47:32,806 --> 01:47:33,806
It's not quite true.

2542
01:47:33,806 --> 01:47:37,306
You have to multiply it by the

2543
01:47:37,306 --> 01:47:40,806
speed of light squared to get energy.

2544
01:47:40,806 --> 01:47:42,806
The main point is that it's conserved.

2545
01:47:42,806 --> 01:47:44,306
Whether or not you multiply it,

2546
01:47:44,306 --> 01:47:46,306
multiply it by the speed of

2547
01:47:46,306 --> 01:47:48,306
light squared is a matter of convention

2548
01:47:48,306 --> 01:47:50,806
and a matter of making it

2549
01:47:50,806 --> 01:47:53,306
consistent with older choices of units.

2550
01:47:53,306 --> 01:47:55,306
Energy has certain units.

2551
01:47:55,306 --> 01:47:58,306
What are the units of energy?

2552
01:47:58,306 --> 01:48:02,306
The units of energy are mass times velocity squared.

2553
01:48:02,306 --> 01:48:04,306
Where did I get that from?

2554
01:48:04,306 --> 01:48:07,306
1 half mv squared is the kinetic

2555
01:48:07,306 --> 01:48:10,306
energy of a particle in ordinary relativistic physics.

2556
01:48:10,306 --> 01:48:13,306
So if pt has anything to do with energy,

2557
01:48:13,306 --> 01:48:16,806
then you better multiply it by c

2558
01:48:16,806 --> 01:48:20,306
squared in order to have units of energy.

2559
01:48:20,306 --> 01:48:23,306
But apart from units, it's just pt.

2560
01:48:23,306 --> 01:48:26,806
Apart from putting in the appropriate powers of c to give

2561
01:48:26,806 --> 01:48:30,306
it the units that we're familiar with when we talk about energy,

2562
01:48:30,306 --> 01:48:33,306
pt is the energy.

2563
01:48:33,306 --> 01:48:34,306
Let's see. Let's go a little bit further.

2564
01:48:34,306 --> 01:48:37,306
Let's work this out and see that it's energy.

2565
01:48:37,306 --> 01:48:39,806
See that it's related

2566
01:48:39,806 --> 01:48:42,306
to nonrelativistic energy, kinetic energy.

2567
01:48:42,306 --> 01:48:43,306
All right.

2568
01:48:43,306 --> 01:48:46,806
First of all, this is mc squared

2569
01:48:46,806 --> 01:48:50,306
times 1 minus v squared over c squared

2570
01:48:50,306 --> 01:48:54,306
to the minus 1 half power.

2571
01:48:54,306 --> 01:48:58,306
Because it's in the denominator, it's to a negative power,

2572
01:48:58,306 --> 01:49:00,306
and because it's a square

2573
01:49:00,306 --> 01:49:02,306
root, it's the power of half.

2574
01:49:02,306 --> 01:49:05,306
Okay.

2575
01:49:05,306 --> 01:49:09,306
Now, I want to work this out for small velocities,

2576
01:49:09,306 --> 01:49:12,306
for velocities very much smaller than the speed of light.

2577
01:49:12,306 --> 01:49:16,306
To do that, we use the binomial theorem.

2578
01:49:16,306 --> 01:49:19,306
The binomial theorem says,

2579
01:49:19,306 --> 01:49:21,806
the main thing for our purposes

2580
01:49:21,806 --> 01:49:24,306
is that what the binomial theorem says

2581
01:49:24,306 --> 01:49:26,806
is that 1 minus a

2582
01:49:26,806 --> 01:49:29,306
small number, let's call it epsilon,

2583
01:49:29,306 --> 01:49:32,806
to any power p is approximately

2584
01:49:32,806 --> 01:49:36,306
equal to 1 minus p epsilon.

2585
01:49:39,306 --> 01:49:41,306
That's the binomial theorem.

2586
01:49:41,306 --> 01:49:47,306
You can, for example, there are higher orders in epsilon,

2587
01:49:47,306 --> 01:49:48,806
plus things of order

2588
01:49:48,806 --> 01:49:50,306
epsilon squared, epsilon cubed, whatever,

2589
01:49:50,306 --> 01:49:52,306
higher orders in epsilon.

2590
01:49:52,306 --> 01:49:56,806
But for example, 1 minus epsilon squared

2591
01:49:56,806 --> 01:50:01,306
is 1 minus 2 epsilon plus epsilon squared.

2592
01:50:01,306 --> 01:50:02,306
Epsilon squared is very, very small.

2593
01:50:02,306 --> 01:50:04,306
We're not interested in it.

2594
01:50:04,306 --> 01:50:08,306
What about 1 minus epsilon cubed?

2595
01:50:08,306 --> 01:50:11,806
That's 1 minus 3 epsilon plus

2596
01:50:11,806 --> 01:50:15,306
things which are order epsilon squared.

2597
01:50:15,306 --> 01:50:17,806
If epsilon squared is very small,

2598
01:50:17,806 --> 01:50:20,306
then 1 minus epsilon to a power

2599
01:50:20,306 --> 01:50:22,306
is just 1 minus the

2600
01:50:22,306 --> 01:50:24,306
power, 1 minus p times epsilon.

2601
01:50:24,306 --> 01:50:28,806
That's what the binomial theorem tells us

2602
01:50:28,806 --> 01:50:33,306
about general powers of 1 minus epsilon.

2603
01:50:33,306 --> 01:50:34,306
All right.

2604
01:50:34,306 --> 01:50:37,306
Now, v squared over c squared is small.

2605
01:50:38,306 --> 01:50:40,306
For a slowly moving particle, v squared

2606
01:50:40,306 --> 01:50:42,306
over c squared is truly very small

2607
01:50:42,306 --> 01:50:44,306
for ordinary velocities.

2608
01:50:44,306 --> 01:50:46,306
And so I can apply this rule.

2609
01:50:46,306 --> 01:50:52,306
And it says that this is mc squared times 1.

2610
01:50:52,306 --> 01:50:54,306
Now, we have a minus from here,

2611
01:50:54,306 --> 01:50:56,306
but we have another minus from here,

2612
01:50:56,306 --> 01:50:59,306
and it comes out to be plus

2613
01:50:59,306 --> 01:51:02,306
1 half v squared over c squared

2614
01:51:02,306 --> 01:51:04,806
plus additional things which are very, very

2615
01:51:04,806 --> 01:51:07,306
much smaller than v squared over c squared.

2616
01:51:08,306 --> 01:51:10,306
The next one will be order

2617
01:51:10,306 --> 01:51:12,306
v fourth over c to the fourth.

2618
01:51:12,306 --> 01:51:16,306
That's impossibly small for any ordinary velocity.

2619
01:51:16,306 --> 01:51:19,806
And so this is basically a

2620
01:51:19,806 --> 01:51:23,306
good approximation for slowly moving objects.

2621
01:51:23,306 --> 01:51:25,306
mc squared times 1 plus 1

2622
01:51:25,306 --> 01:51:27,306
half v squared over c squared.

2623
01:51:27,306 --> 01:51:30,306
And now the rest is familiar.

2624
01:51:30,306 --> 01:51:32,306
It's mc squared.

2625
01:51:32,306 --> 01:51:36,306
You've seen that before.

2626
01:51:36,306 --> 01:51:38,306
But that's only the energy of the energy.

2627
01:51:38,306 --> 01:51:40,306
If the object is at rest.

2628
01:51:40,306 --> 01:51:43,306
If it's moving, there's another

2629
01:51:43,306 --> 01:51:46,306
term which is 1 half m.

2630
01:51:46,306 --> 01:51:49,306
The c squares cancel v squared.

2631
01:51:49,306 --> 01:51:51,806
This is the ordinary Newtonian

2632
01:51:51,806 --> 01:51:54,306
kinetic energy of a moving particle.

2633
01:51:54,306 --> 01:51:57,306
And you add that to the constant mc squared.

2634
01:51:57,306 --> 01:52:01,306
That's what the fourth component of momentum is.

2635
01:52:01,306 --> 01:52:05,306
Or at least for slowly moving nonrelativistic particles,

2636
01:52:05,306 --> 01:52:08,306
the fourth component of momentum is a constant

2637
01:52:08,306 --> 01:52:13,306
which is characteristic of the particle mc squared

2638
01:52:13,306 --> 01:52:18,306
plus the ordinary Newtonian kinetic energy.

2639
01:52:23,306 --> 01:52:26,306
Adding in a constant to the energy of a particle

2640
01:52:26,306 --> 01:52:30,306
if a particle is not allowed to change its mass

2641
01:52:30,306 --> 01:52:34,306
and in Newtonian physics, particles never change their mass.

2642
01:52:34,306 --> 01:52:38,306
If a particle cannot change its mass,

2643
01:52:38,306 --> 01:52:41,306
and you have any number of particles,

2644
01:52:41,306 --> 01:52:44,306
then all of this adds up to some constant.

2645
01:52:44,306 --> 01:52:46,306
And an additional constant in

2646
01:52:46,306 --> 01:52:48,306
the energy doesn't make any difference.

2647
01:52:48,306 --> 01:52:49,806
So the important term in the

2648
01:52:49,806 --> 01:52:51,306
energy when particles are moving slowly

2649
01:52:51,306 --> 01:52:53,306
is this 1 half mv squared.

2650
01:52:53,306 --> 01:52:54,806
That's the term in the

2651
01:52:54,806 --> 01:52:56,306
energy which depends on the velocity.

2652
01:52:56,306 --> 01:52:58,306
It's what we call kinetic energy.

2653
01:52:58,306 --> 01:53:02,806
So that's the four vector

2654
01:53:02,806 --> 01:53:07,306
of momentum includes momentum and energy.

2655
01:53:07,306 --> 01:53:10,306
The conservation of the four vector of momentum

2656
01:53:10,306 --> 01:53:13,306
is the conservation of momentum and energy.

2657
01:53:13,306 --> 01:53:15,306
They go together.

2658
01:53:15,306 --> 01:53:17,806
Even more, when you Lorentz

2659
01:53:17,806 --> 01:53:20,306
transform from one frame to another,

2660
01:53:20,306 --> 01:53:23,306
momentum and energy get mixed up with each other

2661
01:53:23,306 --> 01:53:26,306
because they're components of a four vector.

2662
01:53:26,306 --> 01:53:30,806
So what is energy in one frame becomes

2663
01:53:30,806 --> 01:53:35,306
a combination of energy and momentum in another frame.

2664
01:53:35,306 --> 01:53:40,306
But in every frame, the momentum is conserved.

2665
01:53:40,306 --> 01:53:41,306
That's the important thing.

2666
01:53:41,306 --> 01:53:44,306
Momentum is conserved in every reference frame,

2667
01:53:44,306 --> 01:53:48,306
which means all four components, energy and momentum,

2668
01:53:48,306 --> 01:53:50,806
of an isolated system are the

2669
01:53:50,806 --> 01:53:53,306
same before and after a collision.

2670
